title: New Zealand v Canada: Women’s Rugby World Cup 2025 semi-final – live
summary: Niall McVeigh is providing live updates from the first semi-final taking place at Ashton Gate. Fans can follow along for minute-by-minute reports of the match. Stay tuned for the latest developments and key moments.

title: Morrissey cancels two US shows over ‘credible threat on his life’
summary: A singer has canceled performances in Connecticut and Massachusetts, citing an "abundance of caution." This decision comes shortly after a threat was made in Ottawa. The cancellations highlight ongoing concerns about safety at live events.

title: Estonia requests Nato article 4 consultation after ‘unacceptable’ violation of its airspace by Russian MiG-31s – Europe live
summary: NATO has condemned what it describes as "reckless Russian behaviour" following the interception of three MiG-31 fighters over Estonian airspace. The incident prompted concerns over air safety and increased tensions in the region. NATO underscores its commitment to defending its member states.

title: Senate fails to pass short-term funding bill that would avert government shutdown – US politics live
summary: The Republican-controlled Senate has rejected a continuing resolution passed by the House, which aimed to fund the government. This decision raises concerns about a potential government shutdown. The disagreement highlights ongoing partisan tensions over budgetary issues.

title: Not just a goal machine: new model Haaland can deliver early body blow to Arsenal
summary: Striker is improving within a shifting Manchester City squad and is displaying exceptional goal-scoring form. His performance is raising concerns for even Arsenal's top-tier defense. This development could have significant implications for their upcoming matches.
